link:labelLink.link:label: Superannuation Fund Details Fund Accept Government Contributions Indicator

An indicator to state whether the entity's governing documents (constitution or trust deed) allows it to accept Government contributions such as Superannuation Co-contributions and Low Income Superannuation Contribution.
Valid values are: true = the entity's governing documents allows it to accept Government contributions false = the entity's governing documents do not allow it to accept Government contributions
Superannuation Fund Details Income Stream Paid Indicator
An indicator to state whether the fund paid an income stream to one or more members.
Valid values are: true = the fund paid an income stream to one or more members false = the fund did not pay an income stream to any members
Superannuation Fund Details Actuarial Certificate Indicator
An indicator to specify whether an actuarial certificate was obtained.
Valid values are: true = an actuarial certificate was obtained false = an actuarial certificate was not obtained
Superannuation Payment Benefit Lump Sum Amount
The amount of superannuation lump sum benefits paid.
Superannuation Payment Benefit Lump Sum Code
A code to identify the components of the lump sum paid.

Valid values are: A - Life benefit for member >60 years of age B - Life benefit for member <60 years of age C - Death benefit (to a dependant) D - Death benefit (to a non-dependant) E - Terminal medical condition benefit F - Other lump sum benefit type (for example, Permanent incapacity, Severe financial hardship, Approved compassionate payment) G - Release authority payment (for example, ECT) H - Lump sum benefit paid to a KiwiSaver scheme under Trans-Tasman Retirement Savings Portability arrangements
ECT refers to the Excess Contributions Tax.
Superannuation Payment Benefit Pensions Code
A code to identify the type of income stream paid.

Valid values are: M - Life benefit for Member >60 years of age (other than transition to retirement) N - Life benefit for Member <60 years of age (other than Transition to retirement) O - Transition to retirement P - Death benefit (dependant) where the member died after age 60 or recipient is over 60 years of age Q - Death benefit (dependant) where member died before age 60 and recipient is under 60 years of age R - Other income stream type (for example, Temporary incapacity, Permanent incapacity)
Superannuation Fund Details Member Account Status Code
The status of the member's account.

Valid values are:
Lost = Where the member is lost due to not being contactable with an account balance that is greater than zero.
Inactive = Where the member is lost due to inactivity with an account balance greater than zero.
Found = Where the member was previously reported as lost or inactive and has re-established contact.
Transferred = Where the member was previously reported as lost or inactive and has transferred to another super provider or the Tax Office as unclaimed monies.
Error = Where the member was previously reported in error.
Open = The memberâ€™s account is open and the fund will accept payments
Closed = The memberâ€™s account is closed and will not accept payments
Where a member is both inactive and lost, the member should be reported as 'Lost'.
